                            <comment id="158446" author="yong.fan" created="Tue, 12 Jul 2016 01:09:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The patch has been landed to master.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="158435" author="gerrit" created="Mon, 11 Jul 2016 23:58:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Oleg Drokin (oleg.drokin@intel.com) merged in patch &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/20879/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/20879/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Subject: &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-8298&quot; title=&quot;enabling gss causes possibly misleading warnings from tgt_init_sec_level()&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-8298&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-8298&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; sec: remove obsolete sec_level parameter&lt;br/&gt;
Project: fs/lustre-release&lt;br/&gt;
Branch: master&lt;br/&gt;
Current Patch Set: &lt;br/&gt;
Commit: 881e4d68346be5623c4045dad0d6a50d4954f6fb&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="156852" author="yong.fan" created="Fri, 24 Jun 2016 14:16:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have verified the upgrading case, and updated the class_process_proc_param() in the patch to handle sec_level specially.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="156210" author="yong.fan" created="Mon, 20 Jun 2016 14:18:56 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Still seeing this after &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/19789/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/19789/&lt;/a&gt; landed. I think we can remove the sec_level parameter entirely. Fan Yong do you see any reason to keep it?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Currently, the sec_level is almost meaningless. I am fine to cleanup related code, just one concern about the interoperability issue when upgrade. If some customer has ever specified sec_level as conf parameter, then removing such interface may cause the new server does not recognise the old configuration after upgrading: either confused waring message or start failure. So please verify that, if happened, we can:&lt;br/&gt;
1) simply the interface as empty stub there for some time, or&lt;br/&gt;
2) add some special handling in class_process_proc_param().&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="156203" author="gerrit" created="Mon, 20 Jun 2016 13:37:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;John L. Hammond (john.hammond@intel.com) uploaded a new patch: &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/20879&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/20879&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Subject: &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-8298&quot; title=&quot;enabling gss causes possibly misleading warnings from tgt_init_sec_level()&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-8298&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-8298&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; sec: remove obsolete sec_level parameter&lt;br/&gt;
Project: fs/lustre-release&lt;br/&gt;
Branch: master&lt;br/&gt;
Current Patch Set: 1&lt;br/&gt;
Commit: 9e6bb7777541c02a8ceb9e5634bf1f58544916b9&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="156201" author="jhammond" created="Mon, 20 Jun 2016 13:25:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Still seeing this after &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/19789/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/19789/&lt;/a&gt; landed. I think we can remove the sec_level parameter entirely. Fan Yong do you see any reason to keep it?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="156123" author="yong.fan" created="Sat, 18 Jun 2016 07:15:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It will be disappear after &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-6971&quot; title=&quot;Remove obsolete remote client and &amp;quot;lfs cp|ls|getacl|setacl&amp;quot; commands&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-6971&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-6971&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; patch (&lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/19789/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/19789/&lt;/a&gt;) applied.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="156122" author="yong.fan" created="Sat, 18 Jun 2016 07:13:47 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;After Fan Yong&apos;s patch for &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-6971&quot; title=&quot;Remove obsolete remote client and &amp;quot;lfs cp|ls|getacl|setacl&amp;quot; commands&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-6971&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-6971&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; has landed the I think the &quot;sec_level&quot; functionality will be obsolete. If so then tgt_init_sec_level() can be removed completely and this message will go away.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;With &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-6971&quot; title=&quot;Remove obsolete remote client and &amp;quot;lfs cp|ls|getacl|setacl&amp;quot; commands&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-6971&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-6971&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; patch applied, you will NOT see the misguided message again. So we can close this ticket.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="156064" author="jhammond" created="Fri, 17 Jun 2016 17:39:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;After Fan Yong&apos;s patch for &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-6971&quot; title=&quot;Remove obsolete remote client and &amp;quot;lfs cp|ls|getacl|setacl&amp;quot; commands&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-6971&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-6971&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; has landed the I think the &quot;sec_level&quot; functionality will be obsolete. If so then tgt_init_sec_level() can be removed completely and this message will go away.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
